1 scho ol site. For the purposes of this section, “national criminal
2 history record check” shall have the same meaning as provided for in
3 Section 150.9 of Title 74 of the Oklahoma Statutes. OSBI shall
4 obtain fingerprints of the volunteer and require that the person pay
5 a search fee not to exceed Fifty Dollars ($50.00) or the cost of the
6 search, whichever is the lesser amount. The fee shall be deposited
7 into the OSBI Revolving Fund created pursuant to Section 150.19a of
8 Title 74 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
9 B. A school district board of education or the governing body
10 of a charter school may reimburse volunteers for the cost of the
11 search required by subsection A of this section.
12 C. Each school district board of education and governing body
13 of a charter school shall publish on its website notice of the
14 national criminal history record check required by subsection A of
15 this section and whether the school district or charter school
16 provides reimbursement for the cost of the search, as allowed by
17 subsection B of this section.
18 D. School district or charter school volunteers who meet the
19 criteria provided for in subsection F of Section 5-142 of Title 70
20 of the Oklahoma Statutes may not be required to have a national
21 criminal history record check.
22 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
23 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
24 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
